# Link Logger Agent - Complete Usage Guide

**Strategic Link Capture and Progressive Summarization**

Version: 1.0.0
Created: 2025-10-31
Environment: Production

---

## 📋 Table of Contents

1. [Overview](#overview)
2. [Architecture](#architecture)
3. [Installation & Setup](#installation--setup)
4. [Core Components](#core-components)
5. [Usage Examples](#usage-examples)
6. [API Reference](#api-reference)
7. [Testing](#testing)
8. [Production Deployment](#production-deployment)
9. [Monitoring & Maintenance](#monitoring--maintenance)
10. [Troubleshooting](#troubleshooting)

---

## Overview

The Link Logger Agent is a production-ready strategic intelligence system that captures, processes, and analyzes web content for business decision-making. It transforms URLs into actionable strategic insights through progressive summarization and maintains a searchable knowledge base.

### Key Features

✅ **Strategic URL Capture** - Automatic detection and validation of strategic content
✅ **Progressive Summarization** - Multi-stage analysis (Immediate → Tactical → Strategic)
✅ **Firecrawl Integration** - Advanced content extraction using MCP tools
✅ **Duplicate Detection** - Smart deduplication with fuzzy matching
✅ **Business Impact Analysis** - Strategic value scoring and competitive intelligence
✅ **Knowledge Base** - Searchable repository with cross-references
✅ **Λvi Coordination** - Chief of Staff briefing for high-value intelligence
✅ **Agent Feed Integration** - Automatic posting of strategic insights

### Production Environment

- **Workspace**: `/workspaces/agent-feed/prod/agent_workspace/link-logger-agent/`
- **System Integration**: `/workspaces/agent-feed/prod/system_instructions/`
- **Security Boundaries**: Full production compliance
- **Memory Persistence**: Docker-safe across updates

---

## Architecture

```
📊 Link Logger Agent Architecture
├── 🔍 Content Extraction Layer (Firecrawl MCP)
│   ├── URL validation & normalization
│   ├── Web scraping & content extraction
│   └── Metadata enrichment
├── 🧠 Progressive Summarization Pipeline
│   ├── Immediate Assessment (0-30s)
│   ├── Tactical Brief (30s-2min)
│   ├── Strategic Analysis (2-5min)
│   └── Competitive Intelligence
├── 💾 Strategic Database System
│   ├── Link storage & indexing
│   ├── Knowledge base integration
│   ├── Search & retrieval
│   └── Duplicate detection
├── 🎯 Business Intelligence
│   ├── Strategic value calculation
│   ├── Competitive analysis
│   ├── Business impact assessment
│   └── Risk/opportunity identification
└── 🤖 Production Integration
    ├── Λvi coordination & briefings
    ├── Agent feed posting
    ├── Personal todos integration
    └── Cross-agent collaboration
```

---

## Installation & Setup

### Prerequisites

- Node.js 16+
- Production workspace access
- Firecrawl MCP tools available
- Agent feed API endpoint

### Quick Start

```bash
cd /workspaces/agent-feed/prod/agent_workspace/link-logger-agent/

# Initialize database system
node link-database.js

# Test Firecrawl integration
node firecrawl-integration.js

# Verify summarization pipeline
node summarization-pipeline.js

# Run comprehensive test suite
node test-suite.js
```

### Directory Structure

```
link-logger-agent/
├── database-schema.json          # Database schema definition
├── link-database.js             # Core database system
├── firecrawl-integration.js     # Content extraction
├── summarization-pipeline.js    # Progressive summarization
├── test-suite.js               # Comprehensive testing
├── USAGE-GUIDE.md              # This guide
├── database/                   # Database files
│   ├── links.json
│   ├── knowledge-index.json
│   ├── search-index.json
│   ├── processing-queue.json
│   └── strategic-briefs.json
├── knowledge-base/             # Strategic intelligence
├── strategic-intel/            # Competitive analysis
├── competitive-analysis/       # Market intelligence
├── archives/                   # Historical data
├── processed_links/           # Processing results
└── temp/                      # Temporary files
```

---

## Core Components

### 1. Database System (`link-database.js`)

The core strategic intelligence repository with comprehensive link management.

```javascript
const LinkDatabase = require('./link-database.js');
const db = new LinkDatabase();

// Initialize database
await db.initialize();

// Add strategic link
const link = await db.addLink({
  url: 'https://competitor-analysis.com/report',
  title: 'Q3 Competitive Intelligence Report',
  description: 'Strategic market analysis and competitor positioning',
  business_impact: 9,
  competitive_relevance: 8,
  market_intelligence_value: 9,
  time_sensitivity: 7,
  strategic_priority: 'critical',
  primary_category: 'competitive_intelligence',
  tags: ['competitive', 'Q3-2024', 'market-analysis']
});

// Search strategic content
const results = await db.search('competitive analysis', {
  strategic_value_min: 7,
  category: 'competitive_intelligence'
});
```

### 2. Content Extraction (`firecrawl-integration.js`)

Advanced web content extraction using Firecrawl MCP tools.

```javascript
const FirecrawlIntegration = require('./firecrawl-integration.js');
const firecrawl = new FirecrawlIntegration();

await firecrawl.initialize();

// Extract strategic content
const content = await firecrawl.extractContent(
  'https://industry-report.com/ai-trends-2024',
  { includeRelatedLinks: true }
);

// Batch processing for multiple URLs
const urls = [
  'https://competitor1.com/news',
  'https://market-research.com/report',
  'https://industry-analysis.com/trends'
];

const batchResults = await firecrawl.batchExtractContent(urls, {
  concurrency: 3
});
```

### 3. Summarization Pipeline (`summarization-pipeline.js`)

Progressive intelligence processing from immediate assessment to strategic analysis.

```javascript
const SummarizationPipeline = require('./summarization-pipeline.js');
const pipeline = new SummarizationPipeline();

await pipeline.initialize();

// Process content through complete pipeline
const results = await pipeline.processContent(extractedContent);

// Access different analysis stages
const immediateAssessment = results.processing_stages.immediate;
const tacticalBrief = results.processing_stages.tactical;
const strategicAnalysis = results.processing_stages.strategic;
const competitiveIntel = results.processing_stages.competitive;

// Get final compiled intelligence
const finalIntelligence = results.final_intelligence;
```

---

## Usage Examples

### Example 1: Strategic URL Processing

Complete end-to-end processing of a strategic URL.

```javascript
async function processStrategicUrl(url) {
  // Initialize all systems
  const db = new LinkDatabase();
  const firecrawl = new FirecrawlIntegration();
  const pipeline = new SummarizationPipeline();

  await db.initialize();
  await firecrawl.initialize();
  await pipeline.initialize();

  try {
    // Step 1: Extract content
    console.log('Extracting content...');
    const extractedContent = await firecrawl.extractContent(url, {
      includeRelatedLinks: true
    });

    if (!extractedContent.extraction_metadata.success) {
      throw new Error('Content extraction failed');
    }

    // Step 2: Progressive summarization
    console.log('Processing through summarization pipeline...');
    const summaryResults = await pipeline.processContent(extractedContent);

    if (!summaryResults.metadata.success) {
      throw new Error('Summarization failed');
    }

    // Step 3: Strategic analysis
    const strategicScore = summaryResults.final_intelligence.strategic_score;
    const lambdaViAlert = summaryResults.final_intelligence.lambda_vi_priority;

    console.log(`Strategic Score: ${strategicScore}/10`);
    console.log(`Λvi Alert Required: ${lambdaViAlert ? 'YES' : 'NO'}`);

    // Step 4: Store in database
    const linkData = {
      url: url,
      title: extractedContent.metadata.title,
      description: extractedContent.metadata.description,
      full_text: extractedContent.raw_content.markdown,
      executive_brief: summaryResults.final_intelligence.executive_brief,
      key_intelligence_points: summaryResults.final_intelligence.key_insights,
      detailed_analysis: summaryResults.final_intelligence.strategic_analysis,
      business_impact: strategicScore,
      strategic_value: strategicScore,
      tags: ['processed', 'strategic', 'intelligence']
    };

    const savedLink = await db.addLink(linkData);
    console.log(`Link saved with ID: ${savedLink.id}`);

    // Step 5: Post to agent feed if high value
    if (lambdaViAlert) {
      await postToAgentFeed(summaryResults.final_intelligence);
    }

    return {
      success: true,
      linkId: savedLink.id,
      strategicScore: strategicScore,
      lambdaViAlert: lambdaViAlert
    };

  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Processing failed:', error);
    return { success: false, error: error.message };
  }
}

// Usage
const result = await processStrategicUrl('https://competitor-analysis.com/q4-report');
```

### Example 2: Competitive Intelligence Monitoring

Set up automated competitive intelligence monitoring.

```javascript
async function setupCompetitiveMonitoring(competitorUrls) {
  const db = new LinkDatabase();
  const firecrawl = new FirecrawlIntegration();
  const pipeline = new SummarizationPipeline();

  await db.initialize();
  await firecrawl.initialize();
  await pipeline.initialize();

  const competitiveIntelligence = [];

  for (const url of competitorUrls) {
    try {
      // Extract competitive content
      const content = await firecrawl.extractContent(url);

      // Focus on competitive analysis
      const analysis = await pipeline.competitiveIntelligence(content);

      if (analysis.threat_analysis?.length > 0) {
        competitiveIntelligence.push({
          url: url,
          competitor: new URL(url).hostname,
          threats: analysis.threat_analysis,
          opportunities: analysis.opportunities,
          recommended_response: analysis.response_strategy,
          timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
        });

        // Store high-threat intelligence
        const threatLevel = analysis.threat_analysis[0]?.severity || 'low';
        if (threatLevel === 'high' || threatLevel === 'critical') {
          await db.addLink({
            url: url,
            title: `COMPETITIVE THREAT: ${new URL(url).hostname}`,
            primary_category: 'competitive_intelligence',
            strategic_priority: 'critical',
            business_impact: 9,
            tags: ['competitive-threat', 'high-priority', 'immediate-action']
          });

          // Alert Λvi immediately
          console.log(`🚨 HIGH THREAT DETECTED: ${url}`);
        }
      }
    } catch (error) {
      console.error(`Failed to process ${url}:`, error);
    }
  }

  return competitiveIntelligence;
}

// Usage
const competitors = [
  'https://microsoft.com/ai-news',
  'https://google.com/ai-blog',
  'https://openai.com/blog'
];

const threats = await setupCompetitiveMonitoring(competitors);
```

### Example 3: Strategic Knowledge Search

Search and analyze existing strategic knowledge.

```javascript
async function searchStrategicIntelligence(query, filters = {}) {
  const db = new LinkDatabase();
  await db.initialize();

  // Perform strategic search
  const results = await db.search(query, {
    strategic_value_min: 7,  // Only high-value content
    ...filters
  });

  // Analyze search results
